description.narrative: By 2015, 50% of communities in targeted districts are equipped with knowledge and skills on critical maternal and child survival practices., which contributes to Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2015, rights holders and selected duty bearers use expanded capacities and services to ensure sustained realization of the rights of vulnerable girls and boys
